    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block': 'none';

      return false;

    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.textContent = link.textContent.trim() == s1 ? s2: s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;
    }

                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105576318912', 'post3105576318912')"><pre>        view.view_initkwargs = initkwargs</pre></li>
                  
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105576318912', 'post3105576318912')"><pre></pre></li>
                  
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105576318912', 'post3105576318912')"><pre>        # __name__ and __qualname__ are intentionally left unchanged as</pre></li>
                  
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105576318912', 'post3105576318912')"><pre>        # view_class should be used to robustly determine the name of the view</pre></li>
                  
              </ol>

            <div class="context" id="c3105574389184">
              
                <ol start="41" class="pre-context" id="pre3105574389184">
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        # bound_method has the signature that &#x27;decorator&#x27; expects i.e. no</pre></li>
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        # &#x27;self&#x27; argument, but it&#x27;s a closure over self so it can call</pre></li>
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        # &#x27;func&#x27;. Also, wrap method.__get__() in a function because new</pre></li>
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        # attributes can&#x27;t be set on bound method objects, only on functions.</pre></li>
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        bound_method = wraps(method)(partial(method.__get__(self, type(self))))</pre></li>
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        for dec in decorators:</pre></li>
                
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>            bound_method = dec(bound_method)</pre></li>
                
                </ol>
              
              <ol start="48" class="context-line">
                <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        return bound_method(*args, **kwargs)
                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</pre> <span>…</span></li>
              </ol>

                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>    for dec in decorators:</pre></li>
                  
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>        _update_method_wrapper(_wrapper, dec)</pre></li>
                  
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>    # Preserve any existing attributes of &#x27;method&#x27;, including the name.</pre></li>
                  
                  <li onclick="toggle('pre3105574389184', 'post3105574389184')"><pre>    update_wrapper(_wrapper, method)</pre></li>

  <script>
    function hideAll(elems) {
      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(document.querySelectorAll('ol.pre-context'));
      hideAll(document.querySelectorAll('ol.post-context'));
      hideAll(document.querySelectorAll('div.pastebin'));
    }
    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block': 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.textContent = link.textContent.trim() == s1 ? s2: s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;
    }
  </script>

      hideAll(document.querySelectorAll('div.pastebin'));
    }
    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block': 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.textContent = link.textContent.trim() == s1 ? s2: s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;
    }
  </script>
  
</head>
